# Google Apps Script Setup Instructions (v2 - Performance Update)

To prevent the browser from crashing when the Google Sheet gets thousands of logs, we are implementing **API Filtering**. The script needs to accept a `?sprint=` url parameter and ONLY return rows matching that sprint.

### Update your Code
Open your Google Sheet, go to **Extensions > Apps Script**, and replace your `doGet` function with this updated version:

```javascript
function doGet(e) {
  var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getActiveSheet();
  var data = sheet.getDataRange().getValues();
  
  if (data.length <= 1) {
    return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify([])).setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
  }
  
  var headers = data[0];
  var rows = data.slice(1);
  var result = [];
  
  // Check if the frontend passed a specific 'sprint' filter in the URL
  var targetSprint = e.parameter.sprint;
  
  // Find the index of the 'sprint' column dynamically
  var sprintColIndex = headers.indexOf('sprint');
  
  for (var i = 0; i < rows.length; i++) {
    var rowData = rows[i];
    
    // If a target sprint is requested, skip rows that don't match
    if (targetSprint && sprintColIndex !== -1) {
      // Use loose equality or String casting to handle numbers vs strings
      if (String(rowData[sprintColIndex]) !== String(targetSprint)) {
        continue; 
      }
    }
    
    var obj = {};
    for (var j = 0; j < headers.length; j++) {
      obj[headers[j]] = rowData[j];
    }
    result.push(obj);
  }
  
  return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify(result)).setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
}
```

### Critical: Deploy as a New Version!
Just saving the script won't update the live URL! You **must** go to:
1. **Deploy > Manage deployments**
2. Click the **pencil icon**
3. Under the Version dropdown, select **New version**
4. Click **Deploy**.
